This gives \( 5 \times 5 = 25 \) pairs. - **Case 2**: \( Q \) in C and \( S \) in A. This gives \( 1 \times 5 = 5 \) pairs. - **Case 3**: \( Q \) in C and \( S \) in B. This gives \( 1 \times 5 = 5 \) pairs. 5. **Total Favorable Pairs**: - Summing the cases: \( 25 + 5 + 5 = 35 \). 6. **Probability Calculation**: - The probability is \( \frac{35}{110} = \frac{7}{22} \). 7. **Final Result**: - The fraction \( \frac{7}{22} \) has \( m = 7 \) and \( n = 22 \), so \( m + n = 29 \). \[ \boxed{29} \]
